text.section:
A licensed real estate salesperson may obtain an associate real estate broker license and become affiliated with an additional licensed real estate broker as an associate real estate broker, if the salesperson:
meets the requirements for an associate real estate broker license under § 17-304 of this subtitle;
gives each real estate broker with whom the salesperson currently is affiliated written notice that the salesperson intends to affiliate with an additional real estate broker; and
complies with the application procedures under § 17-307 of this subtitle; or
has previously held an associate real estate broker license or a real estate broker license;
has held a license continuously since initially being licensed as an associate real estate broker or a real estate broker;
obtains, from an additional licensed real estate broker, a commitment providing that the salesperson shall become affiliated with the broker as an associate real estate broker on the granting of an associate real estate broker license to the salesperson;
gives each real estate broker with whom the salesperson currently is affiliated written notice that the salesperson intends to affiliate with an additional real estate broker; and
complies with the application procedures under subsection (j) of this section.

A licensed real estate salesperson may obtain a real estate broker license, if the salesperson:
meets the requirements for a real estate broker license under § 17-305 of this subtitle;
gives each real estate broker with whom the salesperson currently is affiliated written notice that the salesperson intends to obtain a real estate broker license; and
complies with the application procedures under § 17-307 of this subtitle; or
has previously held an associate real estate broker license or a real estate broker license;
has held a license continuously since initially being licensed as an associate real estate broker or a real estate broker;
gives each real estate broker with whom the salesperson currently is affiliated written notice that the salesperson intends to obtain a real estate broker license; and
complies with the application procedures under subsection (j) of this section.

To obtain an additional license, a qualified licensee shall:
submit to the Commission an application on the form that the Commission provides;
if applying for a real estate salesperson or associate real estate broker license, submit to the Commission adequate evidence that the licensee has obtained, from a licensed real estate broker, a commitment providing that the licensee shall become affiliated with the broker as a real estate salesperson or an associate real estate broker on the granting of an additional license to the licensee;
if currently licensed as a real estate salesperson or an associate real estate broker, submit to the Commission a copy of the written notice informing each real estate broker with whom the licensee currently is affiliated that the licensee intends to affiliate with an additional real estate broker or obtain a real estate broker license;
pay to the Commission an application fee set by the Commission; and
submit to the Commission any additional information or documentation that the Commission requires.
